UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2246
1 AN ACT relating to child support.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 403.211 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) An action to establish or enforce child support may be initiated by the parent,
5 custodian, or agency substantially contributing to the support of the child. The
6 action may be brought in the county in which the child resides or where the
7 defendant resides.
8 (2) Notwithstanding the Kentucky Rules of Civil Procedure or any other provision of
9 law, a child shall not:
10 (a) Initiate, intervene in, or otherwise become a party to an action under this
11 section or in any related dissolution of marriage proceeding; or
12 (b) Receive child support payments directly, unless the child is emancipated due
13 to age and still eligible for support in accordance with subsection (3) of
14 Section 2 of this Act.
15 (3) At the time of initial establishment of a child support order, whether temporary or
16 permanent, or in any proceeding to modify a support order, the child support
17 guidelines in KRS 403.212 or 403.2122 shall serve as a rebuttable presumption for
18 the establishment or modification of the amount of child support. Courts may
19 deviate from the guidelines where their application would be unjust or
20 inappropriate. Any deviation shall be accompanied by a written finding or specific
21 finding on the record by the court[,] specifying the reason for the deviation.
22 (4)[(3)] A written finding or specific finding on the record that the application of the
23 guidelines would be unjust or inappropriate in a particular case shall be sufficient to
24 rebut the presumption and allow for an appropriate adjustment of the guideline
25 award if based upon one (1) or more of the following criteria:
26 (a) A child's extraordinary medical or dental needs;
27 (b) A child's extraordinary educational, job training, or special needs;
Page 1 of 9
