UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2246
1 (c) Either parent's own extraordinary needs, such as medical expenses;
2 (d) The independent financial resources, if any, of the child or children;
3 (e) Combined monthly adjusted parental gross income in excess of the Kentucky
4 child support guidelines;
5 (f) The parents of the child, having demonstrated knowledge of the amount of
6 child support established by the Kentucky child support guidelines, have
7 agreed to child support different from the guideline amount. However,[ no
8 such] an agreement shall not be the basis of any deviation if public assistance
9 is being paid on behalf of a child under the provisions of Part D of Title IV of
10 the Federal Social Security Act;
11 (g) Failure by one (1) party to consistently exercise the court-ordered timesharing
12 schedule or timesharing agreement between the parents; and
13 (h) Any similar factor of an extraordinary nature specifically identified by the
14 court which would make application of the guidelines inappropriate.
15 (5)[(4)] "Extraordinary" as used in this section shall be determined by the court in its
16 discretion.
17 (6)[(5)] When a party has defaulted or the court is otherwise presented with
18 insufficient evidence to determine gross income, the court shall order child support
19 based upon the needs of the child or the previous standard of living of the child,
20 whichever is greater. An order entered by default or due to insufficient evidence to
21 determine gross income may be modified upward and arrearages awarded from the
22 date of the original order if evidence of gross income is presented within two (2)
23 years, which would have established a higher amount of child support pursuant to
24 the child support guidelines set forth in KRS 403.212 or 403.2122.
25 (7)[(6)] The court shall allocate between the parents, in proportion to their combined
26 monthly adjusted parental gross income, reasonable and necessary child care costs
27 incurred due to employment, job search, or education leading to employment, in
Page 2 of 9
