UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2246
1 addition to the amount ordered under the child support guidelines.
2 (8)[(7)] (a) Pursuant to 45 C.F.R. sec. 303.31(a)(2),[ for the purposes of] as used in
3 this section, "health care coverage" includes fee for service, health
4 maintenance organization, preferred provider organization, and other types of
5 private health insurance and public health care coverage under which medical
6 services could be provided to a dependent child. If health care coverage is
7 reasonable in cost and accessible to either parent at the time the request for
8 coverage is made, the court shall:
9 1. Order the parent to obtain or maintain coverage;[,] and[ the court shall]
10 2. Allocate between the parents, in proportion to their combined monthly
11 adjusted parental gross income, the cost of health care coverage for the
12 child, in addition to the support ordered under the child support
13 guidelines.
14 (b) A parent[,] who has one hundred percent (100%) of the combined monthly
15 adjusted parental gross income[,] shall be entitled to a reduction in gross
16 income of the entire amount of premiums incurred and paid.
17 (c) The court shall order the cost of health care coverage of the child to be paid
18 by either or both parents of the child regardless of who has physical custody.
19 The court order shall include:
20 1. A judicial directive designating which parent shall have financial
21 responsibility for providing health care coverage for the dependent
22 child, which shall include but not be limited to health care coverage[,] or
23 payments of necessary health care deductibles or copayments;
24 2. If appropriate, cash medical support. "Cash medical support" means an
25 amount to be paid toward the cost of health care coverage, fixed
26 payments for ongoing medical costs, extraordinary medical expenses, or
27 any combination thereof; and
Page 3 of 9
