UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2246
1 3. A statement providing that if the designated parent's health care
2 coverage provides for covered services for dependent children beyond
3 the age of majority, then any unmarried children up to twenty-five (25)
4 years of age who are full-time students enrolled in and attending an
5 accredited educational institution and who are primarily dependent on
6 the insured parent for maintenance and support shall be covered.
7 (d) If health care coverage is not reasonable in cost and accessible at the time the
8 request for the coverage is made, the court order shall provide for cash
9 medical support until health care coverage becomes reasonable in cost and
10 accessible.
11 (9)[(8)] (a) As used in[For purposes of] this section, "reasonable in cost" means that
12 the cost of coverage to the responsible parent does not exceed five percent
13 (5%) of his or her gross income. The five percent (5%) standard shall apply to
14 the cost of adding the child to an existing policy, the difference in the cost
15 between a single and a family policy, or the cost of acquiring a separate policy
16 to cover the child. If the parties agree or the court finds good cause exists, the
17 court may order health care coverage in excess of five percent (5%) of the
18 parent's gross income.
19 (b) As used in[For purposes of] this section, "accessible" means that there are
20 providers who meet the health care needs of the child and who are located no
21 more than sixty (60) minutes or sixty (60) miles from the child's primary
22 residence, except that this section[nothing] shall not prohibit use of a provider
23 located more than sixty (60) minutes or sixty (60) miles from the child's
24 primary residence.
25 (10)[(9)] The initial two hundred fifty dollars ($250) of medical expenses shall be
26 covered by the parent who maintains health insurance for the child or children
27 subject to the order per calendar year, unless the parties have agreed otherwise.
