1 Cabinet for Health and Family Services shall transfer notice of the provision for
2 coverage for the child to the employer, which shall operate to enroll this child in the
3 obligated parent's health plan, unless the obligated parent contests the notice as
4 specified by KRS Chapter 13B.
5 (16)[(15)] Notwithstanding any other provision of this section, any wage or income shall
6 not be exempt from attachment or assignment for the payment of current,[ child
7 support or] owed, or to-be-owed child support.
8 (17)[(16)] A payment of money received by a child as a result of a parental disability
9 shall be credited against the child support obligation of the parent. A payment shall
10 not be counted as income to either parent when calculating a child support
11 obligation. An amount received in excess of the child support obligation shall be
12 credited against a child support arrearage owed by the parent that accrued
13 subsequent to the date of the parental disability, but shall not be applied to an
14 arrearage that accrued prior to the date of disability. The date of disability shall be
15 as determined by the paying agency.
16 (18) Child support payments shall be directed to the parent, custodian, or agency
17 substantially contributing to the support of the child.
18 Section 2. KRS 403.213 is amended to read as follows:
19 (1) The Kentucky child support guidelines may be used by the parent, custodian, or
20 agency substantially contributing to the support of the child as the basis for periodic
21 updates of child support obligations and for modification of child support orders for
22 health care. The provisions of any decree respecting child support may be modified
23 only as to installments accruing subsequent to the filing of the motion for
24 modification and only upon a showing of a material change in circumstances that is
25 substantial and continuing.
26 (2) Application of the Kentucky child support guidelines to the circumstances of the
27 parties at the time of the filing of a motion or petition for modification of the child
Page 6 of 9
XXXX 2/24/2026 10:39 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2246
1 support order which results in equal to or greater than a fifteen percent (15%)
2 change in the amount of support due per month shall be rebuttably presumed to be a
3 material change in circumstances. Application which results in less than a fifteen
4 percent (15%) change in the amount of support due per month shall be rebuttably
5 presumed not to be a material change in circumstances. For the one (1) year period
6 immediately following enactment of this statute, the presumption of material
7 change shall be a twenty-five percent (25%) change in the amount of child support
8 due rather than[ the] fifteen percent (15%)[ stated above].
9 (3) (a) Unless otherwise agreed in writing or expressly provided in the decree,
10 provisions for the support of a child shall be terminated by emancipation of
11 the child unless the child is a high school student when he or she reaches the
12 age of eighteen (18). In cases where the child becomes emancipated because
13 of age, but not due to marriage, while still a high school student, the court-
14 ordered support shall continue while the child is a high school student, but not
15 beyond completion of the school year during which the child reaches the age
16 of nineteen (19) years.
17 (b) Notwithstanding any other provision of law or court interpretation, a child
18 support order shall not be entered, continued, or made retroactive for any
19 period after the child has reached the age of eighteen (18), unless the child
20 was under the age of eighteen (18) at the time the action to establish or
21 enforce child support was initiated.
22 (c) Provisions for the support of the child shall not be terminated by the death of
23 a parent obligated to support the child. If a parent obligated to pay support
24 dies, the amount of support may be modified, revoked, or commuted to a
25 lump-sum payment, to the extent just and appropriate in the circumstances.
26 Emancipation of the child shall not terminate the obligation of child support
27 arrearages that accrued while the child was an unemancipated minor.
