1 (4) The child support guidelines table shall be reviewed at least once every four (4)
2 years by a commission consisting of the following persons:
3 (a) The secretary of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services or a supervisory
4 staff person designated by him or her;
5 (b) Two (2) members of the Kentucky Bar Association who have at least six (6)
6 consecutive years' experience and are presently practicing domestic relations
7 cases, one (1) member from a metropolitan or large urban area and one (1)
8 member from a less populated area;
9 (c) Two (2) Circuit Judges appointed by the Chief Justice of the Kentucky
10 Supreme Court, one (1) from a metropolitan or large urban area, and one (1)
11 from a less populated area;
12 (d) One (1) District Judge appointed by the Chief Justice of the Kentucky
13 Supreme Court;
14 (e) Two (2) county attorneys appointed by the president of the County Attorneys
15 Association, one (1) from a metropolitan or large urban area and one (1) from
16 a less populated area;
17 (f) The Attorney General or his or her designee, who shall be an attorney from
18 his or her office;
19 (g) One (1) person who is a custodial parent;
20 (h) One (1) person who is a noncustodial parent;
21 (i) One (1) person who is a parent with split custody; and
22 (j) One (1) child advocate.
23 The members designated in paragraphs (g) to (j) of this subsection shall be
24 appointed by the Governor from a list of three (3) names for each category
25 submitted by the Cabinet for Health and Family Services. If the status of one (1) of
26 these members changes, the member shall be replaced through appointment by the
27 Governor from a list of three (3) names submitted by the cabinet.
